{"lastModified":1773142078179,"uri":"c::9511793572::vessel::7632f540-d802-11ef-8735-113de0401066","yachtType":["Motor"],"description":"Operating Area: West Mediterranean\n\nExperience M/Y KAMOKA, a 25.89-meter yacht built by Numarine in 2023. This vessel strikes a balance between comfort and performance, making it an ideal choice for charter. With its focus on efficient fuel consumption and an impressive range of up to 3,000 nautical miles, KAMOKA is designed for extended cruising with minimal environmental impact. \n\nKAMOKA accommodates up to 8 guests in 4 well-appointed cabins, including a full-beam master suite with its own study and dressing room. Each cabin is equipped with ensuite facilities and air conditioning, ensuring a comfortable stay. The versatile cabin layout makes it suitable for families or couples. \n\nKAMOKA's interior is designed with a modern, understated elegance. Light colors, natural materials, and large windows create a welcoming atmosphere. The spacious saloon and dining area offer panoramic views, perfect for relaxing or hosting gatherings.\n\nOutdoor living areas include a shaded flybridge for alfresco dining, sunbathing on the foredeck, and a well-designed aft deck. For those seeking adventure, the yacht is equipped with a range of water toys, including jet skis, seabobs, paddleboards, and more. \n\nPowered by twin MAN engines, KAMOKA cruises comfortably at 10 knots, reaching a top speed of 13 knots. Its efficient fuel usage allows for extended journeys across the West Mediterranean, whether exploring\nsmaller bays or cruising along the French Riviera, Corsica, or Sardinia. \n\nCharter M/Y KAMOKA and enjoy a seamless blend of performance, comfort, and sustainable cruising.","blueprint":{"name":"KAMOKA","images":["/media/media::image::a::vessel::7632f540-d802-11ef-8735-113de0401066::assets::946b3f20-d804-11ef-9c48-c16c70df715f/{imageVariant}","/media/media::image::a::vessel::7632f540-d802-11ef-8735-113de0401066::assets::94af7410-d804-11e